<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="14" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="14">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="14">
<bibRefCitation author="Martens, E von" journalOrPublisher="Revue de zoologie et de botanique africaines" pageId="19" pageNumber="30" refId="B36" refString="Martens, E von, 1879. Die Gattung Neritina. Systematisches Conchylien Cabinet, II. 10, 303 pp." title="Die Gattung Neritina. Systematisches Conchylien Cabinet, II. 10, 303 pp." year="1879">Martens (1879)</bibRefCitation>
synonymised 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Issel" authorityYear="1865" class="Gastropoda" family="Neritidae" genus="Theodoxus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Archaeogastropoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="doriae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="14">Theodoxus doriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the species reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Issel, A" journalOrPublisher="Fjaerde Serien" pageId="19" pageNumber="30" refId="B32" refString="Issel, A, 1865. Catalogo dei Molluschi raccolti dalla Missione Italiana in Persia, aggiuntavi la descrizione delle specie nuove o poco note. Memorie della Reale Accademia delle Scienze di Torino, (Ser. II) 23 [1866]: 387-439, 3 tavv. Torino. [Separatum: pp. 1-55, 3 tavv. Stamperia Reale, Torino 1865.]." title="Catalogo dei Molluschi raccolti dalla Missione Italiana in Persia, aggiuntavi la descrizione delle specie nuove o poco note. Memorie della Reale Accademia delle Scienze di Torino, (Ser. II) 23 [1866]: 387 - 439, 3 tavv. Torino. [Separatum: pp. 1 - 55, 3 tavv. Stamperia Reale, Torino 1865.]" year="1865">Issel (1863)</bibRefCitation>
from S Iran, with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" class="Gastropoda" family="Neritidae" genus="Theodoxus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Archaeogastropoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="fluviatilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="14">Theodoxus fluviatilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Later on, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mansoorian, A" journalOrPublisher="Iranian Journal Public Health" pageId="19" pageNumber="30" pagination="77 - 82" refId="B40" refString="Mansoorian, A, 2000. Some freshwater snails from Northern Iran. Iranian Journal Public Health 29 (1-4): 77 - 82" title="Some freshwater snails from Northern Iran." volume="29" year="2000">Mansoorian (2000)</bibRefCitation>
described the operculum of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Issel" authorityYear="1865" class="Gastropoda" family="Neritidae" genus="Theodoxus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Archaeogastropoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="doriae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="14">Theodoxus doriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which has only a rib, no peg. However, the shell illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mansoorian, A" journalOrPublisher="Iranian Journal Public Health" pageId="19" pageNumber="30" refId="B39" refString="Mansoorian, A, 1994. Freshwater snails of Iran. Scientific publication of School of Public Health &amp; Institute of Public Health Research, Technical series 2145: 1374." title="Freshwater snails of Iran. Scientific publication of School of Public Health &amp; Institute of Public Health Research, Technical series 2145: 1374." year="1994">Mansoorian (1994)</bibRefCitation>
agrees well with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" class="Gastropoda" family="Neritidae" genus="Theodoxus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Archaeogastropoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="fluviatilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="14">Theodoxus fluviatilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Thus we follow 
<bibRefCitation author="Martens, E von" journalOrPublisher="Revue de zoologie et de botanique africaines" pageId="19" pageNumber="30" refId="B36" refString="Martens, E von, 1879. Die Gattung Neritina. Systematisches Conchylien Cabinet, II. 10, 303 pp." title="Die Gattung Neritina. Systematisches Conchylien Cabinet, II. 10, 303 pp." year="1879">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Martens’">Martens'</normalizedToken>
(1879)
</bibRefCitation>
synonymisation of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Issel" authorityYear="1865" class="Gastropoda" family="Neritidae" genus="Theodoxus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Archaeogastropoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="doriae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="14">Theodoxus doriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" class="Gastropoda" family="Neritidae" genus="Theodoxus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Archaeogastropoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="fluviatilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="14">Theodoxus fluviatilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Our samples revealed onlythe presence of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" class="Gastropoda" family="Neritidae" genus="Theodoxus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Archaeogastropoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="fluviatilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="14">Theodoxus fluviatilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="14" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="14">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="14">
W- to Central-Palaearctic. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" class="Gastropoda" family="Neritidae" genus="Theodoxus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Archaeogastropoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="fluviatilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="14">Theodoxus fluviatilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been considered by many authors to be an exclusively European species (see e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Zhadin, VI" journalOrPublisher="Turkish Journal of Zoology" pageId="19" pageNumber="30" refId="B61" refString="Zhadin, VI, 1952. Mollusks of Fresh and Brackish Waters of the U.S.S.R. Academie of Sciences of the Union of Soviet Socialist Republics (translated by the Israel Program of Scientific Translations, Jerusalem 1965), xvi + 368 pp." title="Mollusks of Fresh and Brackish Waters of the U. S. S. R. Academie of Sciences of the Union of Soviet Socialist Republics (translated by the Israel Program of Scientific Translations, Jerusalem 1965), xvi + 368 pp." year="1952">Zhadin 1952</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gloeer, P" journalOrPublisher="Die Tierwelt Deutschlands" pageId="19" pageNumber="30" refId="B22" refString="Gloeer, P, 2002. Die Suesswassergastropoden Nord- und Mitteleuropas. Bestimmungsschluessel, Lebensweise, Verbreitung. Die Tierwelt Deutschlands 73, 327 pp." title="Die Suesswassergastropoden Nord- und Mitteleuropas. Bestimmungsschluessel, Lebensweise, Verbreitung." volume="73" year="2002">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Glöer">Gloeer</normalizedToken>
2002
</bibRefCitation>
). But 
<bibRefCitation author="Bourguignat, JR" journalOrPublisher="Chalamelle Aine, Paris" pageId="19" pageNumber="30" refId="B11" refString="Bourguignat, JR, 1864. Malacologie de l'Algerie. Histoire naturelle des animaux mollusques terrestres et fluviatiles. Chalamelle Aine, Paris, 380 pp." title="Malacologie de l'Algerie. Histoire naturelle des animaux mollusques terrestres et fluviatiles." year="1864">Bourguignat (1864)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Brown, DS" journalOrPublisher="Taylor &amp; Francis, London" pageId="19" pageNumber="30" refId="B12" refString="Brown, DS, 1994. Freshwater Snails of Africa and their Medical Importance. 2nd ed. Taylor &amp; Francis, London, 608 pp." title="Freshwater Snails of Africa and their Medical Importance. 2 nd ed." year="1994">Brown (1994)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="van Damme, D" journalOrPublisher="Dr. W. Junk Publishers, Dordrecht" pageId="19" pageNumber="30" refId="B15" refString="van Damme, D, 1984. The Freshwater Mollusca of Northern Africa. Dr. W. Junk Publishers, Dordrecht, 164 pp." title="The Freshwater Mollusca of Northern Africa." year="1984">Van Damme (1984)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned it from NW Africa (Morocco, Algeria). Records of this species in Turkey (
<normalizedToken originalValue="Yıldırım">Yildirim</normalizedToken>
1994), and in Iran, confirm its wide distribution. However, it does not occur in Siberia (Vinarski, pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
